# Form autocomplete

Always disable **browser** autocomplete on ERP forms. This does not apply to custom in-app pickers (`AutocompleteField`, `MachineAutocomplete`, spotlight search, etc.).

## Required

- Every `<form>` must include `autoComplete="off"`.
- Every native `<input>`, `<textarea>`, and `<select>` must include `autoComplete="off"`.
- Do **not** use `autoComplete="username"`, `email`, `tel`, `current-password`, or `new-password`.

## Div-based editors

If a screen uses a `<div>` instead of `<form>` (e.g. purchase order), wrap fields in `<form autoComplete="off" onSubmit={(e) => e.preventDefault()}>` or ensure each field has `autoComplete="off"`.

## Reference

`FormAutoCompleteGuard` in `frontend/src/components/FormAutoCompleteGuard.jsx` enforces this at runtime; still set attributes in JSX for clarity.
